240 grams Diced British Chicken Thigh
150 grams Green Beans
2 nest(s) Egg Noodle Nest
100 grams Bulgogi Sauce
25 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
15 grams Sriracha Sauce
5 grams Roasted White Sesame Seeds
50 milliliter(s) Water

Boil a full kettle.
Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the chicken, 8-10 mins.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the green beans.
Next, pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the noodles and green beans, 4 mins.
Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

When the chicken is cooked, stir in the bulgogi, soy, sriracha and water (see pantry).
Simmer, 1-2 mins.
Mix in the cooked noodles and beans. Add another splash of water if needed.

Share the noodles between your bowls.
Sprinkle over the sesame seeds.